Derek,

Good to hear you have a release!  However, I'm having trouble with 
the ANJI download.  I can't unzip it.  It returns the message, "The 
compressed (zipper) folder is invalid or corrupted."  Let me know 
when you get a chance to check it because I want to test it before 
adding all the links.

ken

--- In neat@yahoogroups.com, Derek James <djames@g...> wrote:
> Well, we're finally releasing ANJI (Another NEAT Java 
Implementation),
> version 1.0.
> 
> Sorry to say there's no handy GUI, but hopefully you'll find it
> reasonably well-designed and documented.
> 
> You can visit our main site here:
> 
> http://anji.sourceforge.net
> 
> Or download the distribution directly from here:
> 
> https://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=101005
> 
> The Documents section of our website has links to a Quick Start, 
the
> API Specifications, and an explanation of the parameters, with
> recommended settings.
> 
> Ken...could you go ahead and add a link from the NEAT FAQ and other
> relevant locations?  (Of course, you might want to put the caveat 
that
> it doesn't work *exactly* like NEAT.) ;)
> 
> We look forward to anyone who uses the implementation and might 
wish
> to contribute to helping improve future versions.  At the very 
least,
> we wouldn't mind using you guys as guinea pigs to just download it 
and
> give it a spin, then offer any feedback.
> 
> Derek
